\item
Co-Inventor, U.S.\/ Patent No.~6,385,765,
``Specification and Verification for Concurrent Systems with Graphical and
Textual Editors''  (May 2002).
\end{enumerate}

\subsection*{Synergistic Activities: Five Examples}
\begin{enumerate}
\item
Developed, along with Michael Kifer, the OSP and OSP~2 courseware for
teaching undergraduate operating systems.  OSP, which has been
used in over 100 institutions worldwide since 1991, is available
via anonymous ftp from \verb+ftp.cs.sunysb.edu/~ospftp/+.  The OSP
users guide is published as {\it OSP:  An Environment for
Operating System Projects}, Addison-Wesley, Reading, MA (1991).  A 2007
textbook on OSP~2, entitled \emph{Introduction to Operating System Design and
Implementation: The OSP 2 Approach}, has been published by Springer Verlag.
\item
Developed, along with Paris C.~Kanellakis, what has come to be known
as \emph{KS-partitioning}, the first algorithm for deciding
bisimulation equivalence of finite-state processes.
\item
One of the developers, along with C.R.\ Ramakrishnan, I.V.\
Ramakrishnan and D.S.\ Warren, of the XMC model checker.  XMC is a
research tool developed with the support of NSF ESS grant
CCR-9705998 and is available on the web at
\url{http://www.cs.sunysb.edu/~lmc/}.
\item
Member: Editorial boards for ACM TOCL, STTT, LMCS and FMSD; Steering
committee for the CONCUR conference series; and IFIP Working Groups~2.2
(member emeritus) and~1.8.
\item
Co-Founder and President of Reactive Systems, Inc., which sells tools and
services for automated testing \& validation of embedded-software designs
based on co-founders' federally funded research.
\end{enumerate}

